21 SECTION 4. ORS 418.607 is amended to read:
22 418.607. It is the intent of the Legislative Assembly that siblings who are foster children have
23 certain essential rights, including but not limited to the following:
24 (1) To obtain substitute care placements together whenever safe and appropriate.
25 (2) To maintain regular contact and visits with siblings while placed both in and out of substi-
26 tute care placements, including regular in-person visits, contact by telephone and electronic
27 communication[, as safe and appropriate], except as limited, denied or prohibited by court order
28 under section 1 of this 2026 Act.
29 (3) To be provided with transportation to maintain contact and have visits with siblings.
30 (4) To be placed with foster parents and assigned caseworkers who have been provided with
31 training on the importance of sibling relationships.
32 (5) [To ensure that contact with siblings will be encouraged in any adoptive or guardianship
33 placement, as safe and appropriate.] To ensure that contact with siblings will be regularly
34 maintained, encouraged and facilitated in any adoptive or guardianship placement, except as
35 limited, denied or prohibited by court order under section 1 of this 2026 Act.
36 (6) To have a sibling contact plan that has been developed as a result of the active engagement
37 and participation of siblings and that is complied with as part of any substitute care placement.
38 (7) [To have more private or less restrictive communication with siblings as compared to commu-
39 nications with others who are not siblings, as safe and appropriate.] To have private and unre-
40 stricted communication with siblings except as limited, denied or prohibited by court order
41 under section 1 of this 2026 Act.
42 (8) To be immediately and timely notified of the birth of a sibling or placement changes or
43 catastrophic events affecting a sibling, [as safe and appropriate] in a developmentally appropriate
44 and trauma-responsive manner.
45 (9) With respect to a foster child’s rights under this section:
